function y = linesine(x, c, m, amplitude, phase, period)% LINESINE computes a linear term combined with a sinusoidal oscillation.%% Inputs:%   x        - Input value(s) (scalar or vector).%   c        - Constant term of the linear function.%   m        - Slope of the linear function.%   amplitude - Amplitude of the sine wave.%   phase    - Phase shift of the sine wave (same units as x).%   period   - Period of the sine wave.%% Output:%   y - Output of the combined line and sine function evaluated at x.% Compute the outputy = c + m .* x + amplitude .* sin(2 * pi * (x - phase) / period);